26
00:01:30,320 --> 00:01:33,560
collect their accounts receivable faster,

27
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:36,980
and then the top-performing companies hold

28
00:01:36,980 --> 00:01:39,850
less than half the inventory.

29
00:01:39,850 --> 00:01:44,760
So as we're going to talk about in the cash flow class,

30
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:47,790
working capital items like accounts receivable

31
00:01:47,790 --> 00:01:51,130
and inventories tie up cash.

32
00:01:51,130 --> 00:01:53,370
So if you have money in inventories,

33
00:01:53,370 --> 00:01:55,290
