60
00:03:50,810 --> 00:03:54,470
The LIFO of cost flow assumption gives us a more accurate income

61
00:03:54,470 --> 00:03:55,640
statement.

62
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:58,040
The FIFO cost flow assumption gives us

63
00:03:58,040 --> 00:04:00,610
a more accurate balance sheet.

64
00:04:00,610 --> 00:04:04,120
Why is it important to understand the distinction

65
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:06,750
between LIFO and FIFO?

66
00:04:06,750 --> 00:04:10,320
Because we have to be able to compare across firms.

67
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:14,790
There's a lot of industries where one firm is a LIFO firm

68
00:04:14,790 --> 00:04:17,459
and one firm is a FIFO firm.

69
00:04:17,459 --> 00:04:20,790
So adjusting for the LIFO reserve

70
00:04:20,790 --> 00:04:26,030
is what we do to adjust for comparability.

